parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt system can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the inability of the seat belt to properly restrain the driver or passenger.
symptoms: The seat belt locks up and won't move
the seat belt does not catch in an accident
the shoulder belt goes forward with the owner and the lap belt breaks
the motorized shoulder belt will not release from its housing
the seat belt stays in the open position
and the seat belt does not retract on the driver's side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the inability of the seat belt to properly restrain the driver or passenger.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle fails to buckle
the red piece inside the buckle breaks

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tail light electrical system can cause the tail lights to malfunction or go out, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The right rear tail lights go out when the headlights are on and the brakes are applied
the left tail light is dim
the brake light stays on even when the brakes are not applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A misadjusted throttle body can cause the vehicle to hesitate or surge forward unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stumbles upon acceleration
the engine revs excessively before accelerating
the vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
the vehicle accelerates as if the cruise control is engaged (even if it's not equipped).
